This September the people of Scotland get to vote on whether to go their own way from us lot down South. I wouldn't blame them if they vote yes, I suspect if I was born and lived up that way I'd be tempted too, if only from the heart rather than the head. But on a personal note as an Englishman living down in Sheffield it would be a disaster. Mainly because it will probably mean we'll be condemned to a permanent Conservative government but also because I feel more at home in the landscape of certain parts of Scotland than I do in most of the rest of the UK. Something I was reminded of during last week in Assynt and on Skye.<br /><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-HIkpBpKnGtE/U2FQwylaVvI/AAAAAAAABqQ/SDsDu5tKAgI/s1600/DSC06987small.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-HIkpBpKnGtE/U2FQwylaVvI/AAAAAAAABqQ/SDsDu5tKAgI/s1600/DSC06987small.jpg" height="110" width="320" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-rga7uRVnkKk/U2FQwxX9BWI/AAAAAAAABqM/G3PzGLVb66E/s1600/DSC06995small.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-rga7uRVnkKk/U2FQwxX9BWI/AAAAAAAABqM/G3PzGLVb66E/s1600/DSC06995small.jpg" height="213" width="320" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-juqEWltanqQ/U2FQxvgpeTI/AAAAAAAABqY/EY-XMaYHyZ8/s1600/DSC06996small.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-juqEWltanqQ/U2FQxvgpeTI/AAAAAAAABqY/EY-XMaYHyZ8/s1600/DSC06996small.jpg" height="72" width="320" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-oaZiedMkdYg/U2FTdIAt-BI/AAAAAAAABrA/3O1Inu3SsQk/s1600/DSC06865small.jpg